James de Villiers, News24OR Tambo International Airport (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Counterfeit takkies worth about R2.8m were seized at OR Tambo International Airport over the Easter weekend, SARS said on Tuesday.Customs officials found 2 380 pairs of sports shoes, weighing 956kg, during a routine inspection of a cargo shed, spokesperson Sandile Memela said in a statement.The consignment came from Hong Kong.They were handed over to the brand holders&rsquo; intellectual property lawyers to explore possible criminal prosecution.Memela did not want to disclose further information, saying that doing so might interfere with the investigation. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.